s://api.github.com/users/ilikerobots/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ilikerobots/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ilikerobots/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ilikerobots/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ilikerobots/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ilikerobots/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ilikerobots/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":48863778,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw0ODg2Mzc3OA==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/labels/!%20Bug","name":"! Bug","color":"8152e0","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2020-02-29T13:13:17Z","updated_at":"2020-02-29T13:13:17Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"NONE","body":"### UIkit Version\r\n3.3.3\r\n\r\n### Actual Behavior\r\nIf a svg with a CORS header is loaded via img tag with uk-svg , then the resulting XMLHttpRequest to retrieve the image will be rejected, despite having CORS authorization.\r\n\r\nThe issue is described by drdek's answer here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/31732533/s3-cors-always-send-vary-origin/34496683#34496683.  To quote:\r\n\r\n> Browser (Chrome) ask the server using a regular <img> or <script> tag. If the server is in the same domain it does not includes an CORS headers.\r\n> Server (S3) returns the resource. If no Origin header was present in the request it does not attach CORS headers in the reply as they are redundant.\r\n> Browser (Chrome) try and get the resource again using AJAX, but this time doesn't really go to the server but looks at the cached resource.\r\n> Browser (Chrome) The cached version does not have CORS headers. It will drop the request as Access-Control-Allow-Origin violation or other related problems.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction Link\r\nhttps://codepen.io/ilikerobots/pen/LYVLVWx\r\n\r\nNote the animation will not work if the page is loaded with cache enabled.  If cache is disabled (e.g. via dev tools) the animation will work since the requests are not cached with missing CORS info.\r\n\r\n### Workaround\r\n\r\nAs noted by drdek's answer in the SO link above, a workaround is to add `crossorigin='use-credentials'` to the image link, forcing chrome to send CORS credentials initially.\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/4139","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/4139/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/4139/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/4139/events","html_url":"https://github.com/uikit/uikit/issues/4139","id":571738320,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU1NzE3MzgzMjA=","number":4139,"title":"W3C CSS + JS validation errors during minification","user":{"login":"sylvaincaillot","id":4845910,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ4NDU5MTA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/4845910?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot","html_url":"https://github.com/sylvaincaillot","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/sylvaincaillot/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":48863778,"node_id":"MDU