; /* equivalent to right in LTR, and left in RTL */\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, only Firefox supports these values right now.\r\n\r\nIt would be really useful if UIKit provided similar classes, defined like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n/* in the LTR normal CSS file: */\r\n.float-start { float: left; }\r\n.float-end { float: right }\r\n\r\n/* in the RTL CSS file: */\r\n.float-start { float: right; }\r\n.float-end { float: left; }\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow, as far as I can tell, that is how `uk-float-right` and `uk-float-left` are currently defined, but that is confusing naming, and one person already has reported this as an issue. https://github.com/uikit/uikit/issues/394\r\n\r\nNote that these proposed classes are not exactly the same behaviour as the new CSS values `inline-start` and `inline-end`, as the new CSS values are clever enough to know the `dir` of the current and parent element. I suppose you could use `:dir` CSS selector to simulate this."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/4056","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/4056/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/4056/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/4056/events","html_url":"https://github.com/uikit/uikit/issues/4056","id":533927919,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU1MzM5Mjc5MTk=","number":4056,"title":"Adding a new \"attr\" option to \"uk-toggle\" in the same way \"cls\" works","user":{"login":"htkm","id":6189096,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYxODkwOTY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/6189096?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/htkm","html_url":"https://github.com/htkm","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/htkm/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/htkm/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/htkm/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/htkm/starred