"created_at":"2019-09-14T08:41:07Z","updated_at":"2019-09-14T08:42:37Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Hi, I would like to make a feature request:\r\n\r\n**Request**\r\nCurrently, the active state for a link on `navbar`, `nav` and `dropdown` can only be set by placing `.uk-active`on the `li` element. However, I would like to request if we could give the user the flexibility to have the same behaviour by placing the `uk-active` class to the `a` element.\r\n\r\n**Rationale**\r\nI'm facing an issue where it is impossible to place the `.uk-active` on the `li` element in a part of my application without breaking the dropdown behaviour of the dropdown menu for the navbar.\r\n\r\nI'm using Svelte and I'm trying to create a component that encapsulates the behaviour of detecting route change and adding the `uk-active` class to the `li` element but I wasn't able successfully to do that without sacrificing menu dropdowns. Hence I resorted to adding the `uk-active` class to the `a` element and then styling it consistently to the active links in my custom stylesheet, but I feel that it would be beneficial to add it to uikit framework to give the users the flexibility to style an active link either by adding `uk-active` to either of the `a` or `li` elements for similar cases.\r\n\r\n**Suggested Solution**\r\nWe could make the similar ammendments wherever applicable across the `dropdown.less`, `nav.less` and `navbar.less` files:\r\n```\r\n// From this\r\n.uk-navbar-nav > li.uk-active > a {\r\n    color: @navbar-nav-item-active-color;\r\n    .hook-navbar-nav-item-active;\r\n}\r\n\r\n// to this\r\n.uk-navbar-nav > li.uk-active > a,\r\n.uk-navbar-nav > li > a.uk-active {\r\n    color: @navbar-nav-item-active-color;\r\n    .hook-navbar-nav-item-active;\r\n}\r\n```"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3977","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3977/labels{/nam