d_at":"2019-07-23T13:26:46Z","updated_at":"2019-07-23T13:26:46Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Currently we have `uk-container-expand-left` and `uk-container-item-padding-remove-left` which works well, however it makes the grid different as it offsets the container. This means something like this: https://i.imgur.com/sZfBrXc.jpg not really possible as `uk-width-1-2` will no longer be the center of the document.\r\n\r\nCurrently I have created a bit of javascript which you can use uk-expand=\"left/right/both\" as you can see here:\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar _ = UIkit.util;\r\n\r\nfunction expand() {\r\n        _.each( _.$$('[uk-expand]'), function(el) {\r\n            var side = _.attr(el, 'uk-expand');\r\n\r\n            // Reset Margin\r\n            if( side == \"right\" || side == \"both\" ) _.css(el, { marginRight: 0 });\r\n            if( side == \"left\" || side == \"both\" ) _.css(el, { marginLeft: 0 });\r\n\r\n            // Calculate distance to edge\r\n            var bound = el.getBoundingClientRect();\r\n\r\n            if( side == \"right\" || side == \"both\" ) _.css(el, { marginRight: -(window.innerWidth - bound.right) });\r\n            if( side == \"left\" || side == \"both\" ) _.css(el, { marginLeft: -bound.left });\r\n        });\r\n}\r\nexpand();\r\n```\r\nThis can be used with `uk-panel` for example. It would be good to have it implemented correctly to open up more layout options."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3922","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3922/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3922/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3922/events","html_url":"https://github.com/uikit/uikit/issues/3922","id":471579713,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU0NzE1Nzk3MTM=","number":3922,"title":"Button position absolute and Off-canvas","user":{"login":"goodwin74","