me for each Drupal site we build. It would be nice if UIKit had a way to handle custom icons by simply adding svg elements inline.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction Link\r\n\r\nWhat currently happens:\r\nhttps://codepen.io/andy-blum/pen/XyRQZo\r\n\r\nWhat it would be nice to see:\r\nhttps://codepen.io/andy-blum/pen/RqVmpL\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nPlace custom inline svg inside a parent with the uk-icon attribute\r\n`<span uk-icon><svg></svg></span>`\r\n\r\n### What is Expected?\r\nI would expect that the uk-icon attribute & component options would influence the sizing of the svg code inside.\r\n\r\nSpecifically, since the bundled icons get a default width/height of 20x20 px, I would anticipate the custom svg element to be scaled to those dimensions and for the ratio component to accurately resize the icon.\r\n\r\nPerhaps telling UIkit to handle icons this way using:\r\n`<span uk-icon=\"icon:custom;ratio:X;><svg></svg></span>`\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nThe svg element is only influenced by the uk-icon class on its parent element and the relevant css."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3658","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3658/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3658/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3658/events","html_url":"https://github.com/uikit/uikit/issues/3658","id":380239521,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzODAyMzk1MjE=","number":3658,"title":"Feature Request: debounce function","user":{"login":"archonmaster","id":14870774,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0ODcwNzc0","avatar_url":"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/14870774?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/archonmaster","html_url":"https://github.com/archonmaster","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/archonmaster/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/archonmaster/f