TML elements in captions are not encoded regardless if other text present.\r\n2. HTML entities in captions are not decoded (3.3 and 3.4).\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n1. If the caption **starts** with any text, then whole caption is HTML-encoded.\r\n2. If the caption starts with, or only contains, HTML tags, they will be processed as HTML.\r\n3. If the caption contains HTML entities, they will be decoded to HTML **if** the caption starts with regular text.\r\n\r\n### Note\r\nThis also is relevant to Lightbox Panel.\r\n\r\nSo there is no way to safely embed user-controlled data in captions. Even if it's HTML-encoded, it gets decoded back if some text appears before HTML tags.\r\n  \r\n  "},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3110","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3110/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3110/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/3110/events","html_url":"https://github.com/uikit/uikit/issues/3110","id":286071604,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyODYwNzE2MDQ=","number":3110,"title":"Overflow on Tabs","user":{"login":"dignajar","id":507352,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUwNzM1Mg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/507352?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dignajar","html_url":"https://github.com/dignajar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dignajar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dignajar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dignajar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dignajar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dignajar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dignajar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dignajar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dignajar/