kit/uikit\r\n- Look for/ask questions on stack overflow: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/ask?tags=getuikit\r\n\r\n-->\r\n\r\n<!-- BUG REPORT TEMPLATE -->\r\n### UIkit version\r\n<!-- Check if the issue is reproducible with the latest stable version. -->\r\n3.0.0-beta.27\r\n\r\n### Browser\r\nFirefox ( latest ), Chrome ( latest ), Safari ( latest ).\r\n\r\n### Reproduction Link\r\n<!-- A minimal Codepen that can reproduce the bug. -->\r\n<!-- You could start with this template: http://codepen.io/anon/pen/XMpryM -->\r\nhttps://codepen.io/zzseba78/pen/jLELQv\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nResize the window height so there is a small scroll on the page ( Codepen content ). Scroll the page.\r\n\r\n### What is Expected?\r\nParallax animates depending on the viewport height and available scroll distance.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nThe parallax animation is done completely in a short distance of the scroll, it is abrupt and looks weird. If there is a small scroll distance available, for example 1/3 in relationship with the viewport height, it should animate 1/3 of the whole transition."},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/2805","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/2805/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/2805/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uikit/uikit/issues/2805/events","html_url":"https://github.com/uikit/uikit/issues/2805","id":245417959,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNDU0MTc5NTk=","number":2805,"title":"Future Request: Dropbar Component Seperate from Navbar","user":{"login":"reramjiawan","id":15954808,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1OTU0ODA4","avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/15954808?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/reramjiawan","html_url":"https://github.com/reramjiawan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/reramjiawan/followers","following_u